<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1173.105123.figure1>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Male palp of Sinoalaria bicornis (Lin, Li & Jaeger, 2014) A prolateral view B retrolateral view C dorsal view D ventral view. Abbreviations: Co = conductor; Cy = cymbium; EB = embolic base; Em = embolus; MA = median apophysis; Pc = paracymbium; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; SCy = setae on cymbium; Te = tegulum. Scale bars: 0.20 mm." ;
